<subSubSection id="9E99656AFFB9FFB034F0F8E796C696A3" pageId="5" pageNumber="352" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D63C36E1FFB9FFB034F0F8E796C696A3" blockId="5.[151,1437,1862,2034]" pageId="5" pageNumber="352">
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFB9FFB034F0F8E7962D960E" bold="true" box="[151,273,1862,1887]" pageId="5" pageNumber="352">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Frons broad (at mid-length about as wide as width of anterior ocellus) (
<figureCitation id="4EB82A64FFB9FFB03048F8E793BE960E" box="[1071,1154,1862,1887]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–14" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1149,1171]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,623,1127]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[188,1398,623,1127]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13–14. Chvalaea Papp &amp; Földvári. 13–14. Frons. 13. Chvalaea ecuadoriensis sp. nov.; 14. Chvalaea masneri Ale- Rocha; Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612713/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="352">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Scutum entirely brown, pleura yellow, except anepisternum and katepisternum brown; scutellum pale brown. Wing pale brown with vein M 
<subScript id="4A0734A4FFB9FFB034D7F83C978496FA" attach="left" box="[176,184,1949,1963]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="352">1</subScript>
evanescent just before meeting wing margin and vein M 
<subScript id="4A0734A4FFB9FFB03728F83C946B96FA" attach="left" box="[847,855,1949,1963]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="352">4</subScript>
reaching wing margin (
<figureCitation id="4EB82A64FFB9FFB03009F82F93F996F6" box="[1134,1221,1934,1959]" captionStart="FIGURES 45–52" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1529,1551]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,450,1499]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,447,1507]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 45–52. Chvalaea Papp &amp; Földvári. Wings. 45. Chvalaea amazonica Ale-Rocha, 2006, holotype ♀; 46. Chvalaea annularis sp. nov., holotype ♂; 47. Chvalaea boliviana Ale-Rocha, 2006, paratype ♀; 48. Chvalaea catarinensis Ale-Rocha, 2006, paratype ♂; 49. Chvalaea ecuadoriensis sp. nov., paratype ♂; 50. Chvalaea masneri Ale-Rocha, 2006, paratype ♀; 51. Chvalaea pulchra Ale-Rocha, 2006, holotype ♀; 52. Chvalaea sinclairi sp. nov., holotype ♂. Abbreviations: bm = basal medial cell; br = basal radial cell; cua = anterior cubital cell; CuA+CuP = anterior branch of cubital vein + posterior branch of cubital vein; dm = discal medial cell; M 1 = first branch of media; M 4 = fourth branch of media; R 1 = anterior branch of radius; R 2+3 = second branch of radius; R 4+5 = third branch of radius. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612729/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="352">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
). Legs extensively brownish (
<figureCitation id="4EB82A64FFB9FFB03577F8149659969F" box="[272,357,1973,1998]" captionStart="FIGURES 37–42" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1903,1925]" captionTargetBox="[144,1429,268,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[144,1429,268,1837]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 37–42. Chvalaea Papp &amp; Földvári. Habitus. 37. Chvalaea amazonica Ale-Rocha, 2006, holotype ♀; 38. Chvalaea annularis sp. nov., holotype ♂; 39. Chvalaea boliviana Ale-Rocha, 2006, paratype ♀; 40. Chvalaea catarinensis Ale-Rocha, 2006, paratype ♂; 41. Chvalaea ecuadoriensis sp. nov., paratype ♂. 42. Chvalaea masneri Ale-Rocha, 2006, paratype ♀. Scale bars = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612725/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="352">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
); hind tarsomeres 3–5 with short, blunt, black spine-like ventral setae. Hypandrium with distal margin sub-triangular (
<figureCitation id="4EB82A64FFB9FFB035FEF87896D196A3" box="[409,493,2009,2034]" captionStart="FIGURES 27–32" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1786,1808]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,225,1690]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,220,1732]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 27–32. Chvalaea ecuadoriensis sp. nov. 27–30. Male terminalia (Paratype), phallus highlighted in gray. 27. Hypandrium and epandrium, ventral view; 28. Epandrium with cerci, dorsal view; 29. Hypandrium and epandrium, left lateral view; 30. Hypandrium and epandrium, right lateral view. 31–32. Female terminalia (Paratype). 31. Dorsal view; 32. Ventral view. Abbreviations: sur = surstylus; cerc = cercus; ST = sternite; T = tergite. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612721/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="352">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
