<subSubSection id="9E99656AFFBBFFB234A0FD8692719311" box="[199,1357,551,576]" pageId="7" pageNumber="354" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D63C36E1FFBBFFB234A0FD8692719311" blockId="7.[151,1437,151,776]" box="[199,1357,551,576]" pageId="7" pageNumber="354">
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFBBFFB234A0FD8696729311" bold="true" box="[199,334,551,576]" pageId="7" pageNumber="354">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet refers to the country of origin of all the 
<typeStatus id="09388843FFBBFFB23793FD8993189311" box="[1012,1060,552,576]" pageId="7" pageNumber="354">type</typeStatus>
specimens of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9E99656AFFBBFFB234A0FDE896439256" pageId="7" pageNumber="354" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D63C36E1FFBBFFB234A0FDE896439256" blockId="7.[151,1437,151,776]" pageId="7" pageNumber="354">
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFBBFFB234A0FDE896079333" bold="true" box="[199,315,585,610]" pageId="7" pageNumber="354">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="11834D62FFBBFFB23525FDE8956D9330" authority="Barros &amp; Soares &amp; Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha, 2019" authorityName="Barros &amp; Soares &amp; Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2019" box="[322,593,585,609]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ecuadoriensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFBBFFB23525FDE8956D9330" box="[322,593,585,609]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="354">Chvalaea ecuadoriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFBBFFB2363FFDE8958E9333" bold="true" box="[600,690,585,610]" pageId="7" pageNumber="354">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="FFC45788FFBBFFB2363FFDE8958E9333" box="[600,690,585,610]" pageId="7" pageNumber="354" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="11834D62FFBBFFB2368EFDE894589330" authorityName="Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2006" box="[745,868,585,609]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="masneri">
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFBBFFB2368EFDE894589330" box="[745,868,585,609]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="354">C. masneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar species, including the pronotum black, variable color of the pleura, usually the brown proepimeron. However, 
<taxonomicName id="11834D62FFBBFFB237D7FDCA935193D2" authority="Barros &amp; Soares &amp; Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha, 2019" authorityName="Barros &amp; Soares &amp; Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2019" box="[944,1133,619,643]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ecuadoriensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFBBFFB237D7FDCA935193D2" box="[944,1133,619,643]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="354">C. ecuadoriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFBBFFB23014FDCB93F093D2" bold="true" box="[1139,1228,618,643]" pageId="7" pageNumber="354">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="FFC45788FFBBFFB23014FDCB93F093D2" box="[1139,1228,618,643]" pageId="7" pageNumber="354" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is larger and more robust than 
<taxonomicName id="11834D62FFBBFFB2357BFD2D96AB93F5" authorityName="Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2006" box="[284,407,652,676]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="masneri">
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFBBFFB2357BFD2D96AB93F5" box="[284,407,652,676]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="354">C. masneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the scutum is uniformly brown, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="11834D62FFBBFFB237F5FD2D933193F5" authorityName="Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2006" box="[914,1037,652,676]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="masneri">
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFBBFFB237F5FD2D933193F5" box="[914,1037,652,676]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="354">C. masneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the scutum is dark brown to black. 
<taxonomicName id="11834D62FFBBFFB234F0FD0C96969394" authority="Barros &amp; Soares &amp; Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha, 2019" authorityName="Barros &amp; Soares &amp; Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2019" box="[151,426,685,709]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ecuadoriensis" status="sp. nov">
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFBBFFB234F0FD0C96969394" box="[151,426,685,709]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="354">Chvalaea ecuadoriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFBBFFB235D2FD0C95329397" bold="true" box="[437,526,685,710]" pageId="7" pageNumber="354">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="FFC45788FFBBFFB235D2FD0C95329397" box="[437,526,685,710]" pageId="7" pageNumber="354" rank="species">sp. nov</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
have an entirely brown hind tibia and in 
<taxonomicName id="11834D62FFBBFFB23062FD0F93B99394" authorityName="Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2006" box="[1029,1157,686,709]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="masneri">
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFBBFFB23062FD0F93B99394" box="[1029,1157,686,709]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="354">C. masneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the hind tibia is black, yellowish near extreme base. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName id="11834D62FFBBFFB23618FD6E940093B7" authority="Barros &amp; Soares &amp; Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha, 2019" authorityName="Barros &amp; Soares &amp; Freitas-Silva &amp; Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2019" box="[639,828,718,742]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ecuadoriensis" status="sp. nov">
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFBBFFB23618FD6E940093B7" box="[639,828,718,742]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="354">C. ecuadoriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFBBFFB23724FD6F94A493B6" bold="true" box="[835,920,718,743]" pageId="7" pageNumber="354">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="FFC45788FFBBFFB23724FD6F94A493B6" box="[835,920,718,743]" pageId="7" pageNumber="354" rank="species">sp. nov</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
have the frons broad, while in 
<taxonomicName id="11834D62FFBBFFB23090FD6E924E93B7" authorityName="Ale-Rocha" authorityYear="2006" box="[1271,1394,719,742]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Chvalaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="354" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="masneri">
<emphasis id="E4F7EAF3FFBBFFB23090FD6E924E93B7" box="[1271,1394,719,742]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="354">C. masneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the frons is very narrow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
